The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Cellphone theft arrest
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       Cellphone theft arrest
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	A youth was arrested in the port area on Sunday on charges of buying a stolen cellphone.        
	Mohammed Babar, a relative of former Forward Bloc MLA Mohammed Yakub, had bought a Nokia 1200 handset from Mohammed Ilias, alias Sonu, for a few hundred rupees, said a police officer.        
	Ilias was arrested on Saturday. He had stolen the phone from Pulakdhani Ram on July 10. Ram was in a hotel on Karl Marx Sarani when his phone was stolen, said Anand Kumar, the deputy commissioner of police (port).        
	Ram lodged an FIR with South Port police station.         
	Ilias said that he had sold the phone to Babar. We have arrested Babar on charges of receiving a stolen item, said an officer.                                                                                                                                                                         
